The elderly in Port Shepstone in KwaZulu-Natal say they are afraid of losing their place in line. Senior Government officials visited various pay points in the area. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Day two of the grant payments got off to a good start on Tuesday. Some pensioners and people with disabilities were able to collect their grants on Monday but there were long queues and there was no social distancing at pay points. In Atteridgeville some of the buses that were supposed to ferry pensioners to pay points didn't arrive. COVID-19: Sassa pays out grants early Social Development Minister Lindiwe Zulu has urged grant collectors to maintain social distancing. The Department of Transport eased the lockdown regulations for public transport this week to make it easier for social grant recipients amid the coronavirus pandemic.